---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Sidebar from "../components/Sidebar.astro";
import FloatingControls from "../components/FloatingControls.astro";
---

<!doctype html>
<html>
  <Header title="Design Process | Rolando Aguilar Ordaz" />
  <body>
    <FloatingControls />
    <div class="content">
      <Sidebar selectedItem="design-process" />
      <nav class="main" style="padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0;">
        <div class="container" style="max-width: 100%; width: 100%;">
          <div class="back-nav-container" style="margin-left: 48px;">
            <a href="/" class="back-nav-button w-inline-block">
              <Icon name="lucide:chevron-left" class="back-nav-img" />
              <div data-i18n="nav.back">Back</div>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div
            class="content-container"
            style="padding: 0 48px; margin-bottom: 24px;"
          >
            <div class="section-title" data-i18n="design.title">Design Process</div>
            <p class="lead" style="font-size: 18px; width: 100%; max-width: 1200px;" data-i18n="design.lead">
              Una mirada a mi metodología de trabajo, desde entender el problema
              inicial hasta convertirlo en un producto funcional.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-container">
            <div class="timeline-track">
              <!-- Item 01 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">01</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step1.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:search" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    DT: Inquiry & Empathy
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step1.desc">
                    Design Thinking phase to connect with real users.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 02 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">02</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step2.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:flask-conical" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    DT: Prototyping & Selection
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step2.desc">
                    Building two competitive prototypes and selecting the winning solution.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 03 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">03</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step3.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:file-text" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    SDLC: Engineering & Documentation
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step3.desc">
                    Technical engineering rigor: Creating SRS/SDS and architecture.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 04 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">04</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step4.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:git-graph" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    SDLC: Flows & Wireframes
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step4.desc">
                    Translating user stories into flow diagrams and wireframes.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 05 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">05</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step5.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:palette" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    Design: High Fidelity
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step5.desc">
                    Final interface design applying my philosophy of intuitive beauty.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 06 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">06</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step6.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:code-2" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    SDLC: Iterative Development
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step6.desc">
                    Sprint-based coding with constant validations.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Item 07 -->
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <div class="timeline-number">07</div>
                  <div class="timeline-title" data-i18n="design.step7.title">
                    <Icon name="lucide:rocket" class="bento-icon" size={20} />
                    Delivery & Launch
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline-desc" data-i18n="design.step7.desc">
                    Consolidating documentation and system delivery.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Symbology/Legend -->
          <div class="content-container" style="padding: 0 48px; margin-bottom: 48px; margin-top: -40px;">
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 24px; font-size: 14px; opacity: 0.7; color: #fff;">
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <strong style="color: #fff;">DT:</strong> Design Thinking
              </div>
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;">
                <strong style="color: #fff;">SDLC:</strong> Software Development Life Cycle (Ciclo de Vida de Desarrollo de Software)
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Secondary Content Section -->
          <div
            class="content-container"
            style="padding: 0 48px; margin-bottom: 80px;"
          >
            <div class="section-title" style="margin-bottom: 32px;" data-i18n="design.principles.title">
              Principios de Diseño
            </div>
            <div
              style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 24px;"
            >
              <!-- Info Card 01 -->
              <div
                class="card"
                style="padding: 32px; transition: transform 0.2s ease;"
              >
                <h4
                  style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;"
                >
                  <Icon name="lucide:brain" class="bento-icon" size={24} />
                  <span data-i18n="design.principles.1.title">Cognitive Psychology</span>
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="project-desc"
                  style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0;"
                  data-i18n="design.principles.1.desc"
                >
                  El diseño no debe ser una barrera, sino una herramienta
                  compasiva. Me pongo en los zapatos de los usuarios finales
                  para asegurar que cada interacción conecte perfectamente con
                  la necesidad humana detrás de la pantalla.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- Info Card 02 -->
              <div
                class="card"
                style="padding: 32px; transition: transform 0.2s ease;"
              >
                <h4
                  style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;"
                >
                  <Icon name="lucide:users-2" class="bento-icon" size={24} />
                  <span data-i18n="design.principles.2.title">Collective Impact</span>
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="project-desc"
                  style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0;"
                  data-i18n="design.principles.2.desc"
                >
                  Huyo de la estética "fría y corporativa". Creo en herramientas
                  que inspiren fuerza de trabajo, empoderando colectivamente a
                  los usuarios en entornos lúdicos o interactivos, fomentando
                  comunidad en lugar de burocracia.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- Info Card 03 -->
              <div
                class="card"
                style="padding: 32px; transition: transform 0.2s ease;"
              >
                <h4
                  style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;"
                >
                  <Icon name="lucide:sparkles" class="bento-icon" size={24} />
                  <span data-i18n="design.principles.3.title">Democratized Aesthetics</span>
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="project-desc"
                  style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0;"
                  data-i18n="design.principles.3.desc"
                >
                  No impongo un estilo único y terco. Cada producto es distinto
                  y requiere adaptabilidad visual. Me mantengo estudiando nuevas
                  herramientas y afilando el diseño apoyándome en las tendencias
                  más recientes y óptimas del mercado global.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
